content: Hola, I‚Äôm new here just wanted to check about what‚Äôs going on in RI!! My name is Jess
Hi Jess, I'm Traci! I'm still learning how to use Discord!
What up Rhody?! Also pretty new to Discord - but glad we have our own channel! <:clap:1252804035489169459>

This is just a reminder that you can sign up to phone bank, canvass, get trainings  or take other actions at https://events.democrats.org/ in your state or in one of our battleground states (NC, PA, GA, NH, WI, PA, MI, AZ, NV). Volunteers like you make all the difference! We look forward to seeing you at an event soon.
Let me know if you need help using Discord! I just arrived on the server, but I‚Äôve used Discord for years.

<@1079463559513255936> and <@1039264170002108496> I made a little video to help you manage the overwhelm of learning how to use this Discord community.
https://youtu.be/cA32MMsN61g
Hello!  I‚Äôm Joanne from RI. Just wondering if the campaign will be taking action here in our blue state and if this is the best way to hear about it.
Hi Joanne welcome from RI. The best place to hear about events and actions is https://events.democrats.org/ you can filter with your zip code to find local events.
<@568257600228032512> Thank you!  I‚Äôll check it out.
## [Rhode Island Voter Information](https://www.vote.org/state/rhode-island/)
Pinned a message.
Hello RI! What a convention‚Ä¶ so excited for tonight n looking forward to volunteering to make sure we win

I have lots of family and friends who are very excited about Harris for President. But, I know they wouldn‚Äôt want to canvass or phone bank. So I thought I could have a postcard writing party. But I can‚Äôt find any information on how to get addresses for voters in the swing states or even if there are Harris Walz postcards available.  Who should I contact for this info?
That‚Äôs a great idea, unfortunately I have  no idea where to get addresses or if there are postcards.
The DNC should be paying for materials and distributing them. I‚Äôd be happy to fill out cards, but I cannot afford the postage. This is what donations go to. Isn‚Äôt there a training on this?

Hi <@1274514774423502860> , <@1275560249612439697> , <@806959475797524522> I suggest going to https://events.democrats.org and type "postcard" in the filter, it will show you the postcard events near you.

<@1274514774423502860> I found this link on FB to order postcards. Orders some, hope it‚Äôs legit ‚Ä¶ https://m.facebook.com/story.php?story_fbid=pfbid0t5r88cN87AXExokaEPL8NyVVES5U2nJdJtJJfs4Z2JkCZf7Z3KWHN5mHhA54XTxBl&id=100064623194078
https://action.momsrising.org/survey/2024_Postcards_May?source=aae&aktmid=tm11066304.2B5Vsn&akid=a28886217.3520273.5Im-e4&t=3&utm_campaign=outreach&utm_medium=email&utm_source=actionkit
Or this if not on FB
hi <@1275560249612439697> if you type "postcard" in the events page it will give you events that are for blue voters and events near you. https://events.democrats.org

Carolyn, there are no events of any kind listed in RI. Maybe the Harris campaign doesn‚Äôt have a presence here yet?  I checked the Progressive Turnout Project as people in the general chat suggested, but their search for people to write postcards is complete. I‚Äôm assuming it‚Äôs just early and that RI will start mobilizing soon‚Ä¶ hopefully.
Sandrine,  Great find!  I ordered some too!  And I expected to have to pay for the postage‚Ä¶ so having the postcards already stamped is a bonus!  Thanks for sharing!
I found out after the fact that they were non partisan, not sure that was the way to go haha but I had ordered some
Same here. I looked for events here but there‚Äôs nothing
It‚Äôs ok‚Ä¶ the purpose of their campaign is to get out the vote. And I think that‚Äôs important too!
Absolutely!
We will just have to keep checking back. Maybe when there are some organizers in RI, they will reach post something here.
<@1274514774423502860> somebody confirmed that the link I posted is for all parties and told me to check out turnoutpac.org

Sandrine, I scrolled through the momsrising Facebook page and they shared lots of posts about the Democratic ticket and convention. They also support many of the policies of the democrats. I think it‚Äôs ok to participate in their postcard program to get out the vote. But I also want to send postcards to swing states for Kamala Harris. I‚Äôll check out turnoutpac.org. Thanks!
I will check it too, haven‚Äôt had time today, will do both.
Turnoutpac.org is the same as the Progressive Turnout Project that I looked at earlier. Their postcard project is closed. They have 265,000 people to send 36 million postcards. It‚Äôs amazing!

I know that in the past and currently there have been letter writing campaigns in/out of South and Newport County. I‚Äôve been meaning to try to reach out to folks I know who‚Äôd been involved with organizing those efforts. ADHD has not been my friend there. But I do intend to do so and then I can let you know. If I don‚Äôt, feel free to poke me!
Thanks! Please keep me posted!

For anyone who is interested, I am hosting an Out for Harris-Walz Debate Watch Party on Tuesday, Sept. 10 in partnership with the Human Rights Campaign and the Rhode Island Democratic Party LGBTQ+ Caucus 

https://events.democrats.org/event/680805/

<a:star_wave:1269735420359606369> Hey, Team! We know you want to help make a difference! Did you know though that hosting a debate watch party is an amazing way to get involved and bring people together? <a:rainbow_heart_scribble:1269029739432120465> It‚Äôs all about good vibes, great conversations, and getting folks fired up for the election. Your watch party could be the spark that motivates someone to vote! <a:PinkFlames:1252802562659193004>  [Register your watch party](https://events.democrats.org/c/host-a-debate-watch-party/event/create/) to get access to all sorts of resources for throwing a successful debate watch party, including a [Host Information Session](https://events.democrats.org/event/677337/). <a:ThanksRainbow:1278765693579431967>
Let's do this. Who's having a debate watch party?

Same issues here. I'm so disappointed in RI. I even wrote a letter to RI's  Democratic Committee. I'm calling Reed, Whitehouse, and Magaziner tomorrow to complain. We need a fun rally that we can have ourselves.
Colleen, please let us know if you receive a reply from anybody‚Ä¶ I‚Äôd be interested to hear about it.
https://www.mobilize.us/voteriders/event/564817/?referring_vol=6684605&rname=Michael&share_context=event_details&share_medium=copy_link

Absolutely Joanne! Maybe if another of us call, they'll do something. They pulled Tim Walz into Newport by invitation only for donors. How about constituents? I have a Dr's. Appt. Thurs. in the same building that the Election Division is in. I'm going to stop in and talk to them too.
Good idea‚Ä¶ I‚Äôll reach out to them too.
Sounds good! Why can't RI do a rally for Harris? Florida has done multiple rallies organized by senior citizens there.
My wife and I just registered to attend the Watch Party on September 10th. <@1280302501505273995> thank you for sharing the link!
Debate Watch party at the Dark Lady in Providence, you can register with link provided by Anthony above üîù
The Democratic Party didn't call me back. Magaziner's staff was really receptive. They're starting a phone bank, but we need some enthusiasm in this state. Did you have any better luck?

I haven‚Äôt received a reply from the RI Democratic Party either (maybe they are busy with the primary on Tuesday?). I did see Magaziner‚Äôs phone bank listed on mobilize, as well as the debate watch party being held by the LGBTQ caucus. I have 100 GOTV postcards coming this week and another 100 at the end of September. So, I‚Äôll be able to gather family and friends together to write some postcards.

I talked to Magaziner's office too. I heard there's a national women's march on Nov. 2nd. Hopefully, RI will be part of it. I'm doing so many videos on social media and calls. I'm working at the polls, but I'm watching the debate with family and friends immediately after.

I googled the Women‚Äôs March. There‚Äôs a big March planned in Washington D.C.  The website said that local marches will be announced by the end of the month. So, we all need to Save the Date‚Ä¶ November 2!
<@1274514774423502860> thank you for sharing! I‚Äôll be in DC on November 2 üíô
Oh wow!  I‚Äôm jealous!
We have family there, we‚Äôll drive Friday after work, will be there at midnight üòä
